    "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nWhen pressing **directly onto** a song title in a list view, a tap is triggered instead of the long-press action, i.e. the song starts playing instead of the context menu showing.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Go into a listing of songs, e.g. open an album\r\n2. Long-press **directly onto** a song title\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nContext menu should pop up.\r\n\r\n**Screenshots**\r\nSee video here: [vinyl-screenrecord-bug-listview.mp4](https://sx.ix5.org/files/misc/vinyl-screenrecord-bug-listview.mp4)\r\n\r\n**Smartphone (please complete the following information):**\r\n - Device: Sony Xperia XZ2 Compact\r\n - Android Version: 9\r\n - ROM: Stock firmware, June security patch\r\n - Vinyl Music Player Version: 0.22.1\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nI strongly suspect https://github.com/AdrienPoupa/VinylMusicPlayer/pull/172 since neither previous versions nor the upstream Phonograph player seems to have the issue.\r\n",
